gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 114, Celtics 109
gameRecap.excerpt: Led by Anthony Edwards' 38 points, nine rebounds, and seven assists, the Timberwolves defeated the Celtics in overtime, 114-109, handing Boston its first loss of the season. Jaden McDaniels added 20 points for the Timberwolves in the victory, while Jayson Tatum (32 points, five rebounds) and Jaylen Brown (26 points, seven rebounds, four assists) combined for 58 points for the Celtics in the losing effort. The Timberwolves improve to 4-2 on the season, while the Celtics fall to 5-1.
